          <p>the Genki Ball</p>
        </div>
        <div id="site">
          <h1>Select a Site</h1>
          <ol>
            <li>Select a shady area to work; best outdoors on grass</li>
            <li>Have tables and benches available</li>
            <li>Tarps to protect tables</li>
            <li>Water source with hose and water key for water pipe is crucial</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
        <div id="supplies">
          <h1>General Procedure: Supplies</h1>
          <ul>
            <li>Soil</li>
            <li>EM-1 Concentrate</li>
            <li>Molasses</li>
            <li>Rice Bran</li>
            <li>Alumbinum Baking Pans</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div id="soil">
          <h1>Procedure: Preparing The Dry Soil</h1>
          <ol>
            <li>Place soil in a mixing tray (1 bag = 10 to 12 liters of sifted soil)</li>
            <li>Add rice or wheat bran carefully due to its fine particles (800g); mix well</li>
            <li>Prepare the EM mixture:</li>
              <ul>
                <li>Place 800 ml. of water into a 3 to 4 L. container</li>
                <li>Add .5 cup of molasses to the water and mix well (w/ clean hand)</li>
                <li>Add 1 liter of EM-1 and mix well</li>
              </ul>
            <li>Add prepared EM-1 mixture slowly and mix well till soil is rolled and formed into a firm ball. (Donâ€™t use all of the liquid if soil feels too wet)</li>
            <li>Pat the ball so the air pockets are removed</li>
            <li>Add EM mixture or water in small amounts if the ball easily crumbles</li>
            <li>Place 12 balls on layers of newspaper in a baking aluminum pan</li>
            <li>Take balls to the counting area</li>
            <li>Keep balls covered w/ newspaper throughout drying</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
        <div id="storage">
          <h1>Storage: Procedure</h1>
          <ol>
            <li>Cover balls w/ newspaper</li>
            <li>Place them in a area where they will not get wet</li>
            <li>Select an storage area away from direct sunlight</li>
            <li>Allow them to dry slowly (about 2 weeks). Rapid drying = cracking and break-up</li>
            <li>Turn over to all all sides to dry</li>
            <li>Change the newspaper to avoid black mold growth</li>
          </ol>
          <br>
        </div>
